TITLE: Generating Rollback Commands for Flagsmith (Pre v2.151.0)
DESCRIPTION: SQL query to generate Python commands for rolling back migrations in Flagsmith versions earlier than v2.151.0. The query uses the django_migrations table to determine the appropriate rollback commands.
SOURCE: https://github.com/flagsmith/flagsmith/blob/main/docs/docs/deployment/hosting/locally-api.md#2025-04-21_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
select
    concat('python manage.py migrate ',
    app,
    ' ',
    case
        when substring(name, 1, 4)::integer = 1 then 'zero'
        else lpad((substring(name, 1, 4)::integer - 1)::text, 4, '0')
        end
    ) as "python_commands"
from django_migrations
where id in (
    select min(id)
    from django_migrations
    where applied >= 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss'
    group by app
);
```

